{"TopicId":153564,"ForumId":16,"TopicTitle":"Distance to Waypoint?","CreatedByName":"Kobymaru","CreatedById":107372,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-12-15T15:18:16Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Kobymaru","CreatedById":107372,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-12-15T15:18:16Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHi! 1.2 added the amazing possibility to place Waypoints via the KerbNet. However, when activating it for navigation, I can\u0027t find any readout for the distance to the target.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIs there a Stock way to do that?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"bewing","CreatedById":154251,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-12-15T16:55:26Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222888679\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022153564\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221481815096\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022107372\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Kobymaru\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, Kobymaru said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIs there a Stock way to do that?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNope. Sorry.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe best I\u0027ve ever been able to do is to point the nose of my ship directly at the waypoint, and then look along the line of the ship to try to guess exactly the point on the ground where it\u0027s aiming.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Palaceviking","CreatedById":166883,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-12-15T18:30:33Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAre you open to modding?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Kobymaru","CreatedById":107372,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-12-15T19:32:12Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222888998\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022153564\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221481826633\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022166883\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Palaceviking\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, Palaceviking said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAre you open to modding?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI know of Waypoint Manager which shows the distance, but I was just wondering if there is a stock way. I have an answer now, and I\u0027ll just install waypoint manager.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}